---
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro"
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<Layout
  title="About — Matteo Cavallo"
  description="Web engineer based in Paris. A longer take on what I do, why I do it, and the work that brought me here."
>
  <div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pt-28 pb-20 md:pt-32 md:pb-24">
    <header class="mb-12 md:mb-16">
      <h1 class="mb-2 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl">About</h1>
      <p class="font-serif text-neutral-500 italic dark:text-neutral-400">
        Still falling, still learning.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section
      class="mb-20 space-y-6 font-serif text-lg leading-relaxed md:text-xl"
    >
      <p>
        For years, I've worked as a frontend engineer, building interfaces for
        large-scale projects. I've learned precision, structure, and how to make
        complex systems feel simple.
      </p>
      <p>
        But somewhere along the way, I started craving something more personal —
        something that could reflect not just what I do, but why I do it.
      </p>
      <p>This site is where that idea starts to take form.</p>
      <p>
        It's not a portfolio in the traditional sense. It's a living space — a
        place to experiment, to connect dots between design and engineering, to
        explore the balance between logic and emotion.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm learning to move slower. To build with intention. To make things
        that last.
      </p>
      <p>This space will grow with me — changing shape as I do.</p>
    </section>

  </div>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
